               <head>Poetry of Ahli</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by Ahlī</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh89005046" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1369A-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar hi">Persian, Arabic, Hindi</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled collection of poetic compositions in varied forms and genres (ghazalīyāt, muqaṭṭaʿāt, maṭlaʿīyāt, mukhammasāt, and rubāʿīyāt) by the poet, Muḥammad ibn Yūsuf ibn Shihāb Ṣūfī Shīrāzī takhalluṣ Ahlī (d. 942/1535).</p>
                        <p>The concluding area before the colophon quotes verses by Ibn Yamīn (d. 769/1368).</p>
                        <p>Colophon (f. 63v): completed by Muḥammad Amīn (not dated).</p>
                        <p>The first folio has been cut and pasted onto a replacement folio.</p>
                        <p>Tinted papers (pale orange, pale greyish blue).</p>
                        <p>Not foliated.</p>
                        <p>Lacking original binding.</p>
                        <p>Damaged soft brown leather binding (delaminating combed marbled doubleurs, revealing Kaithi text underneath), broken spine.</p>
                        <p>Folios bound; cropped, wormholes, later repairs.</p>
                        <p>Condition fragile.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657193.0x000001 viaf_36817419">Ahlī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_36817419">اهلى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
